# Nuxt Boilerplate – Coding Rules

## Architecture: Feature-Based

```
app/features/<name>/
  components/   feature-local Vue components
  composables/  useFeature.ts  (logic bridge)
  stores/       useFeatureStore.ts (Pinia setup store)
  models/       Pinia ORM entity models
  types/        feature.types.ts
  locales/      en.json
```

Pages are thin wrappers. Global stuff goes in `app/components/shared/`, `app/stores/`, `app/composables/`.

## Rules

**TypeScript**

- Use TypeScript only, fully strict types
- No `any` — ever. Define an explicit type.
- All params and return types must be typed.
- `interface` for objects, `type` for unions.
- Feature types: `features/<name>/types/<name>.types.ts`; global: `app/types/<domain>.types.ts`
- Never define inline types in stores, composables, or components.

**Imports**

- Imports must be grouped into separate blocks separated by a blank line.
- The required block order is:
  1. Node module dependencies
  2. Own custom dependencies
  3. Types
  4. Vue components
- Use `@/` for path aliases instead of `~/`.

**No Comments**

- No inline comments, no JSDoc.
- Name things clearly instead.
- Absolutely no comments are allowed in the code, not even `// TODO:` comments. No exceptions.

**i18n**

- All UI strings via `$t()` — never hardcode text.
- `features/<name>/locales/en.json` → `$t('<name>.key')`
- `app/shared/locales/en.json` → `$t('key')` globally
- English only.

**Pinia**

- Setup store style always: `defineStore('id', () => { ... })`
- Explicit generics on state: `ref<Type>(default)`

**Pinia ORM**

- Models in `features/<name>/models/`
- Decorators: `@Num(0)`, `@Str('')`, `@Bool(false)`

**SCSS & Theme System**

- Themes → `app/assets/scss/themes/` (one file each: `_default`, `_dark`, `_ocean`)
- Theme selector: `[data-theme='<name>']` with HSL primary (`--color-primary-h/s/l`)
- `_variables.scss` = spacing, typography, radii only — never colors
- User custom color: `useThemeStore.setCustomColor(hex)` → overrides H/S/L on `<html>`
- `app/plugins/theme.client.ts` restores saved theme from localStorage
- Components: `<style scoped lang="scss">` in this exact order, BEM naming, CSS vars only

**Auto-Imports — do not import manually**

- Vue: `ref`, `computed`, `reactive`, `watch`, `readonly`, etc.
- Nuxt: `definePageMeta`, `navigateTo`, `useRouter`, `createError`, etc.
- Pinia: `defineStore`
- All from `app/composables/`, `app/stores/`, `app/features/*/composables/`, `app/features/*/stores/`

## Git Commits – Conventional Commits

Format: `type(scope): short description`

| Type | When to use |
|---|---|
| `feat` | New feature or page |
| `fix` | Bug fix |
| `refactor` | Code change with no behavior change |
| `style` | Formatting only (no logic change) |
| `docs` | Documentation, README, agent rules |
| `test` | Adding or updating tests |
| `chore` | Tooling, config, dependencies |
| `build` | Build system changes (nuxt.config, vite) |
| `ci` | CI/CD pipeline changes |
| `perf` | Performance improvement |
| `revert` | Revert a previous commit |

**Scope** = affected feature or area (`auth`, `home`, `i18n`, `deps`, `layout`)

```
feat(auth): add login page and auth store
fix(home): correct hero subtitle alignment
chore(deps): update nuxt to 4.4.5
refactor(auth): extract login logic into useAuth composable
test(home): add HomeHero component integration test
build(nuxt): enable pinia-orm module
```

- Subject: max 72 chars, lowercase, no trailing period
- Body (optional): explain *why*, not *what*
- Breaking change: `feat(auth)!: remove legacy session`
